1
00:00:01,134 --> 00:00:02,201
Look at this.

2
00:00:02,202 --> 00:00:04,937
(Episode 8: Something Is Seriously Wrong)

3
00:00:06,206 --> 00:00:07,273
You're mine now.

4
00:00:07,808 --> 00:00:10,243
We've got you now.

5
00:00:11,712 --> 00:00:13,146
You're stuck with me now.

6
00:00:15,382 --> 00:00:17,083
Hey, Baby Yu Jun Choi.

7
00:00:17,251 --> 00:00:19,418
(YEONJUN has resurrected.)

8
00:00:21,722 --> 00:00:23,590
Give me a kiss, Yu Jun.

9
00:00:25,225 --> 00:00:26,692
(A boop on his nose instead of a kiss)

10
00:00:26,693 --> 00:00:27,626
Ding-dong.

11
00:00:29,062 --> 00:00:30,763
Yu Jun.

12
00:00:30,764 --> 00:00:32,197
I'll teach him what a kiss is.

13
00:00:32,699 --> 00:00:33,632
Give me a kiss.

14
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:35,669
(The first attempt to get a kiss)

15
00:00:35,769 --> 00:00:36,669
He knows his own name.

16
00:00:36,670 --> 00:00:38,204
(I don't know how to give a kiss yet.)

17
00:00:38,338 --> 00:00:39,238
Give me a wink.

18
00:00:41,575 --> 00:00:43,709
- He's improved.
- Great job.

19
00:00:44,211 --> 00:00:45,144
(A celebratory high five)
Hey, Mozzarella Stick.

20
00:00:46,747 --> 00:00:47,613
Try making him come to you.

21
00:00:47,781 --> 00:00:48,782
Hold your hands out.

22
00:00:49,950 --> 00:00:51,918
(On-site service)

23
00:00:53,187 --> 00:00:55,355
- He comes if you reach your hands out.
- We've become a lot closer now.

24
00:00:55,456 --> 00:00:57,023
Yu Jun, do you want some rice crackers?

25
00:00:57,024 --> 00:00:58,558
(Hold my hand.)

26
00:00:58,559 --> 00:01:00,326
But there's a condition.

27
00:01:00,327 --> 00:01:01,628
You have to give me a kiss.

28
00:01:02,095 --> 00:01:02,861
Kissy-kissy.

29
00:01:04,498 --> 00:01:05,331
"Just give it to me."

30
00:01:08,368 --> 00:01:09,134
"What are they saying?"

31
00:01:12,245 --> 00:01:13,906
(Rejected again, he comforts himself
with rice crackers.)

32
00:01:13,907 --> 00:01:15,708
Yu Jun, be careful.

33
00:01:15,709 --> 00:01:16,909
It's too early to give up.

34
00:01:17,611 --> 00:01:19,478
- Did his parents write a note?
- Yes.

35
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:22,481
It says Yu Jun has grown up so much,

36
00:01:22,482 --> 00:01:24,550
and now he's eating regular food...

37
00:01:24,551 --> 00:01:26,586
instead of baby food.

38
00:01:26,587 --> 00:01:27,353
Give him a round of applause.

39
00:01:27,354 --> 00:01:28,921
(I can eat real food now.)

40
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:30,956
- Give it up for him.
- You're in for some real treats now.

41
00:01:31,391 --> 00:01:32,625
Then, we can...

42
00:01:32,626 --> 00:01:34,059
He can eat lots of delicious food.

43
00:01:34,060 --> 00:01:35,027
Yu Jun, how about pork belly?

44
00:01:35,229 --> 00:01:37,397
They wrote down a few recipes for him.

45
00:01:37,398 --> 00:01:38,965
Beef and egg fried rice.

46
00:01:40,434 --> 00:01:41,300
(Learning Yu Jun's lunch menu)

47
00:01:41,301 --> 00:01:42,935
- Okay.
- Egg fried rice is good.

48
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:43,669
It's easy.

49
00:01:43,670 --> 00:01:45,538
Then should we have ramyeon
with the egg fried rice?

50
00:01:45,539 --> 00:01:46,739
Great. Let's have ramyeon.

51
00:01:47,407 --> 00:01:48,974
(Hey, uncle BEOMGYU!)

52
00:01:49,243 --> 00:01:50,243
- What?
- Food for Yu Jun.

53
00:01:50,410 --> 00:01:52,177
(I need you to follow me.)

54
00:01:53,914 --> 00:01:55,715
(Yu Jun is taking BEOMGYU somewhere.)

55
00:01:55,716 --> 00:01:57,250
Where do you want to go?

56
00:01:57,251 --> 00:01:59,685
Where are we going?

57
00:02:01,188 --> 00:02:02,555
You want this? Okay.

58
00:02:02,923 --> 00:02:04,323
At 12:30 p.m.? Or at noon?

59
00:02:04,492 --> 00:02:05,258
Maybe now.

60
00:02:06,059 --> 00:02:07,659
- His lunchtime starts at noon.
- What time is it?

61
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:10,362
It's 10:15 a.m.

62
00:02:11,198 --> 00:02:12,064
Check the ingredients.

63
00:02:12,766 --> 00:02:15,601
Should we make some fine dining
for Yu Jun today?

64
00:02:15,602 --> 00:02:16,702
Fine dining sounds nice.

65
00:02:16,703 --> 00:02:18,371
- Yu Jun.
- Fine dining.

66
00:02:18,705 --> 00:02:19,605
Yu Jun, give me a high-five.

67
00:02:19,773 --> 00:02:21,140
Yu Jun, have you ever been to an omakase?

68
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:22,241
(I don't want to.)

69
00:02:23,210 --> 00:02:24,278
He isn't even looking that way.

70
00:02:24,279 --> 00:02:25,143
(Hold my hand.)

71
00:02:25,144 --> 00:02:26,879
He's been doing
a lot of no-look shots today.

72
00:02:27,314 --> 00:02:29,014
(Yu Jun's personal chef
checks the ingredients.)

73
00:02:29,349 --> 00:02:31,116
(Give it to me already!)

74
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:32,818
Where's Yu Jun?

75
00:02:33,954 --> 00:02:35,922
(I'm here to get some more rice crackers.)

76
00:02:35,923 --> 00:02:36,622
Okay.

77
00:02:38,458 --> 00:02:39,224
High-five.

78
00:02:39,225 --> 00:02:40,559
(YEONJUN.)

79
00:02:40,794 --> 00:02:42,261
He's taking him there to get some more.

80
00:02:42,262 --> 00:02:43,662
No.

81
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:44,797
(Dragging YEONJUN before he stands up)

82
00:02:44,798 --> 00:02:45,731
He's so fast.

83
00:02:46,466 --> 00:02:47,399
Here you go.

84
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,068
(Using the members one by one
as his rice cracker tongs)

85
00:02:53,106 --> 00:02:54,339
Snack.

86
00:02:55,809 --> 00:02:57,376
(This time, he chooses TAEHYUN.)

87
00:02:57,377 --> 00:02:59,111
(Come on.)

88
00:02:59,112 --> 00:03:00,546
Is it me this time?

89
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:02,214
He's finished it...

90
00:03:02,215 --> 00:03:05,318
He's finishing the one in his hand
while asking for more.

91
00:03:05,719 --> 00:03:06,752
You want more?

92
00:03:06,753 --> 00:03:07,653
(Having a rice cracker feast)

93
00:03:07,654 --> 00:03:09,955
- It's so good, right?
- You won't eat your actual meal, then.

94
00:03:10,369 --> 00:03:11,836
Yu Jun, want to go for a ride
on the Pirate Ship?

95
00:03:13,193 --> 00:03:15,294
(Welcome to the magical world
of HEUKALAND.)

96
00:03:15,295 --> 00:03:17,163
Yu Jun is on board the Pirate Ship.

97
00:03:17,164 --> 00:03:19,131
(First course: The Blanket Pirate Ship)

98
00:03:19,132 --> 00:03:19,932
Hold tight.

99
00:03:22,536 --> 00:03:23,502
He doesn't like it.

100
00:03:25,305 --> 00:03:26,272
He escaped from the Pirate Ship.

101
00:03:27,274 --> 00:03:28,140
He glared at you.

102
00:03:28,508 --> 00:03:30,375
- He got off himself?
- Yes.

103
00:03:30,376 --> 00:03:32,378
(The manager of HEUKALAND is
very busy today.)

104
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:33,412
Yu Jun.

105
00:03:36,984 --> 00:03:39,519
(Second course:
I'm going to make myself disappear!)

106
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:41,253
(HEUNINGKAI is gone.)

107
00:03:41,254 --> 00:03:42,422
He's gone.

108
00:03:42,423 --> 00:03:44,223
But HEUNINGKAI was so slow.

109
00:03:44,691 --> 00:03:46,392
- I could see him move.
- Right.

110
00:03:46,393 --> 00:03:47,426
(Looking for him with a magic prop)

111
00:03:47,427 --> 00:03:48,460
He's looking for him with the blanket.

112
00:03:48,938 --> 00:03:50,505
(If I catch you, you're done for.)

113
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:51,397
He wants you to come.

114
00:03:52,966 --> 00:03:53,899
He's after you.

115
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,901
You're playing hide and seek right now.
You have to run away.

116
00:03:56,170 --> 00:03:58,337
- He's excited.
- Are you having fun?

117
00:03:58,338 --> 00:04:00,072
- He's so excited.
- Wasn't he looking for HEUNINGKAI?

118
00:04:01,541 --> 00:04:04,343
(Manager HEUNINGKAI is
preparing something big.)

119
00:04:04,344 --> 00:04:05,310
It's a snake.

120
00:04:05,311 --> 00:04:07,312
(The last course: Safari in HEUKALAND)

121
00:04:08,148 --> 00:04:10,182
(Today's special performance,
the snake show)

122
00:04:11,384 --> 00:04:13,018
(What is he doing?)

123
00:04:14,287 --> 00:04:15,954
It's coming to catch you, Yu Jun.

124
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:18,123
Run now.

125
00:04:18,124 --> 00:04:19,458
Yu Jun is looking at it.

126
00:04:19,465 --> 00:04:20,432
Run away from the snake.

127
00:04:20,894 --> 00:04:21,927
It's coming to get you.

128
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:23,329
(Run!)

129
00:04:25,065 --> 00:04:25,898
(HEUKALAND is closed now.)

130
00:04:26,099 --> 00:04:27,566
- What is he doing?
- He wants rice crackers.

131
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:29,134
- It's your turn now.
- We shouldn't give him anymore.

132
00:04:29,296 --> 00:04:30,269
He just wants to drag him around.
Really?

133
00:04:31,471 --> 00:04:33,906
He's doing so well now,

134
00:04:33,907 --> 00:04:35,874
even without his parents around.

135
00:04:38,178 --> 00:04:41,080
(Instead of the rice cracker,
it's time for takeoff.)

136
00:04:41,081 --> 00:04:43,482
He likes it.

137
00:04:43,483 --> 00:04:46,252
(Transformed from a human bed
into a human airplane)

138
00:04:46,686 --> 00:04:47,653
It looks fun, though.

139
00:04:47,921 --> 00:04:50,923
(The other members must
want to ride it too.)

140
00:04:53,894 --> 00:04:55,127
(SOOBIN's airplane is landing.)

141
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:56,128
Clap!

142
00:04:58,198 --> 00:04:59,632
(Hold my hand.)

143
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:00,666
He's staggering.

144
00:05:02,969 --> 00:05:03,769
Mom.

145
00:05:04,604 --> 00:05:06,572
Yu Jun, here's your mom.

146
00:05:06,573 --> 00:05:08,807
What? Does he want more rice crackers?

147
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:12,411
What? Is he crying?

148
00:05:12,546 --> 00:05:14,714
- What's wrong?
- I can't figure out your mood.

149
00:05:14,715 --> 00:05:15,948
I thought you were having fun.

150
00:05:16,550 --> 00:05:19,252
- We were having a blast.
- He was excited.

151
00:05:19,553 --> 00:05:21,020
What's wrong, Yu Jun?

152
00:05:21,254 --> 00:05:22,588
Mom.

153
00:05:22,589 --> 00:05:24,756
He must be reminded of his mom suddenly.

154
00:05:25,492 --> 00:05:27,560
- As he passed the entrance...
- He just realized that his mom is gone.

155
00:05:27,561 --> 00:05:28,561
He just realized it.

156
00:05:28,562 --> 00:05:29,528
He just realized.

157
00:05:29,529 --> 00:05:30,863
(Emergency!)

158
00:05:31,498 --> 00:05:34,066
(Operation Calm Yu Jun Down begins.)

159
00:05:34,634 --> 00:05:38,203
(First strategy, you cry, and I cry too.)

160
00:05:40,273 --> 00:05:42,808
Yu Jun, why am I crying?

161
00:05:45,579 --> 00:05:46,646
Should we laugh aloud all together?

162
00:05:47,481 --> 00:05:49,715
(Second strategy, you cry, and I laugh)

163
00:05:49,716 --> 00:05:51,150
Yu Jun, it's so much fun.

164
00:05:52,419 --> 00:05:55,421
(Letting out a big laugh at Yu Jun)

165
00:05:55,422 --> 00:05:56,489
Should we give him his pacifier?

166
00:05:56,823 --> 00:05:57,656
- Shall we?
- It's all right.

167
00:05:57,991 --> 00:05:59,024
Yu Jun.

168
00:05:59,292 --> 00:06:01,426
(Follow me.)

169
00:06:01,427 --> 00:06:03,462
Play "Stick With You."

170
00:06:03,463 --> 00:06:04,497
All right.

171
00:06:04,498 --> 00:06:06,932
- Play "Stick With You."
- I'll play it.

172
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:09,101
He's walking well even while crying.

173
00:06:09,102 --> 00:06:10,235
Wait.

174
00:06:10,470 --> 00:06:12,871
(Why is he taking your shirt off?)

175
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:15,441
You miss your mommy?

176
00:06:15,476 --> 00:06:17,253
(Playing "Stick With You")

177
00:06:17,277 --> 00:06:18,143
What's this?

178
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:20,879
Yu Jun, your mommy is here.

179
00:06:21,615 --> 00:06:22,715
It's me, your mommy.

180
00:06:25,485 --> 00:06:26,819
He likes the pacifier better.

181
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:30,289
How do you like it?
You picked this song as your favorite.

182
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:34,093
(I know this song.)

183
00:06:35,128 --> 00:06:36,195
(Music replaced due to copyright)

184
00:06:36,196 --> 00:06:38,197
It's magical. He stops crying
as soon as this song starts.

185
00:06:39,332 --> 00:06:40,299
Look at him.

186
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:41,466
Let's get into the groove!

187
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:44,770
(Swaying)

188
00:06:45,205 --> 00:06:45,704
(Swaying)
(Swaying)

189
00:06:48,175 --> 00:06:49,942
(Let me sway my body too.)

190
00:06:49,943 --> 00:06:50,843
What's this song?

191
00:06:51,044 --> 00:06:52,411
Is this a dream?

192
00:06:55,882 --> 00:06:58,917
(Efforts to make Yu Jun smile)

193
00:07:01,454 --> 00:07:02,788
He has his pacifier in the wrong way.

194
00:07:03,056 --> 00:07:04,523
We should make it a hit,
like "Baby Shark."

195
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:05,924
He's smiling.

196
00:07:07,327 --> 00:07:09,094
He stops crying when he hears this song.

197
00:07:10,563 --> 00:07:11,563
(And he even dances too.)

198
00:07:11,564 --> 00:07:13,098
- It's hot.
- Are you happy now?

199
00:07:14,234 --> 00:07:15,100
Are you happy?

200
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:16,702
(Yu Jun is so happy.)

201
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:19,571
Yu Jun, look at the camera
for an ending pose.

202
00:07:19,973 --> 00:07:21,040
Pose for the ending part.

203
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:22,342
Mozzarella Stick, the ending fairy.

204
00:07:23,743 --> 00:07:25,844
(Mozzarella Stick, the ending fairy)

205
00:07:25,845 --> 00:07:26,645
So cute.

206
00:07:27,047 --> 00:07:27,880
(So into Mozzarella Stick)

207
00:07:27,881 --> 00:07:29,549
- Mozzarella Stick.
- Should I play it one more time?

208
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:31,951
(Peace has returned.)

209
00:07:31,952 --> 00:07:33,219
Yu Jun, how about taking a bath?

210
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:34,520
- Baby Yu Jun.
- Yu Jun.

211
00:07:35,088 --> 00:07:36,889
I saw him play with it the other day.

212
00:07:36,890 --> 00:07:37,990
- Really?
- Yes.

213
00:07:38,191 --> 00:07:39,124
That's nice.

214
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:41,728
Shall we begin, then?

215
00:07:41,729 --> 00:07:43,996
Should I go and run the water
for the bathtub?

216
00:07:44,064 --> 00:07:44,930
That's a good idea.

217
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:48,133
(Getting Yu Jun's bubble bath ready)

218
00:07:49,536 --> 00:07:54,006
(I hope Yu Jun likes playing
with bubbles.)

219
00:07:55,041 --> 00:07:55,974
Tickling!

220
00:07:56,877 --> 00:07:58,344
I'm gonna tickle you.

221
00:07:59,346 --> 00:08:00,246
I'm tickling you.
(Stop it, seriously.)

222
00:08:02,349 --> 00:08:03,249
Is it ticklish?

223
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:05,751
- I'm tickling you.
- It feels weird, doesn't it?

224
00:08:06,853 --> 00:08:09,488
(The tub is filled with bubbles already.)

225
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:10,890
The tub's already pretty full.

226
00:08:11,224 --> 00:08:12,090
- Yes.
- Let me check.

227
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:13,432
(Double-checking the temperature)

228
00:08:13,433 --> 00:08:15,394
- It's warm.
- Yes, it's nice and warm.

229
00:08:16,663 --> 00:08:18,097
I think it's perfect.

230
00:08:18,765 --> 00:08:20,199
- I'll bring Yu Jun, then.
- Okay.

231
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,266
(Yu Jun's bubble bath is ready.)

232
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:22,802
Yu Jun.

233
00:08:22,803 --> 00:08:23,635
Let's go take a bath.

234
00:08:24,471 --> 00:08:26,472
- Let's take a bath.
- Yu Jun, it's bubble time.

235
00:08:27,874 --> 00:08:29,107
(Shaking his head)

236
00:08:29,676 --> 00:08:31,509
Did you see him shake his head just now?

237
00:08:31,510 --> 00:08:33,578
- He's really good at expressing himself.
- I know.

238
00:08:33,780 --> 00:08:35,147
He shakes his head
when he doesn't like it.

239
00:08:35,148 --> 00:08:36,515
Yu Jun, you need to take a bath.

240
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:38,517
Let's have a bubble bath.

241
00:08:38,518 --> 00:08:39,685
(Playing with bubbles will be fun.)

242
00:08:39,686 --> 00:08:40,519
You don't want to?

243
00:08:41,054 --> 00:08:41,820
You don't want to?

244
00:08:42,389 --> 00:08:43,956
I bet you'll have fun once you get in.

245
00:08:44,557 --> 00:08:46,625
TAEHYUN, play "Bubble Pop."

246
00:08:47,594 --> 00:08:48,427
Yu Jun.

247
00:08:48,728 --> 00:08:49,695
Yu Jun, want a bubble bath?

248
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:51,830
(We'll make it fun for you.)

249
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:53,232
- Bubble pop
- Bubble pop

250
00:08:53,233 --> 00:08:55,167
(Music replaced due to copyright issues)

251
00:08:55,168 --> 00:08:56,369
- Yu Jun.
- Bubble pop

252
00:08:56,970 --> 00:08:59,338
You pull off this style well too.

253
00:08:59,839 --> 00:09:01,506
(I love this song.)

254
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:02,842
He can move to the rhythm.

255
00:09:02,843 --> 00:09:05,211
Take his clothes off while dancing.

256
00:09:05,946 --> 00:09:09,682
(Just enjoy the music.)

257
00:09:09,683 --> 00:09:12,919
It's like a magical girl transformation
from a cartoon.

258
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:13,819
Keep dancing.

259
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:15,588
(Transformation of the magical baby,
Yu Jun)

260
00:09:15,589 --> 00:09:17,823
He's taking his clothes off himself.

261
00:09:17,958 --> 00:09:19,325
This baby is on fire!

262
00:09:21,094 --> 00:09:24,664
(The members look more excited
than Yu Jun.)

263
00:09:24,665 --> 00:09:27,499
(My heart grew like a bubble)

264
00:09:31,671 --> 00:09:32,872
Pull it up over his head first.

265
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:34,673
You just need to get his head out.

266
00:09:34,674 --> 00:09:37,075
- His arm is stuck.
- Arm first.

267
00:09:37,076 --> 00:09:38,078
Try taking his arm out first.

268
00:09:39,646 --> 00:09:41,714
(I'm suddenly sad.)

269
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:44,516
(Bursting out crying in the end)

270
00:09:44,517 --> 00:09:46,551
There aren't any tears, anyway!

271
00:09:47,821 --> 00:09:49,255
What's wrong?

272
00:09:50,023 --> 00:09:51,523
You don't like it?

273
00:09:51,524 --> 00:09:54,259
- Oh, my gosh.
- He burst into tears anyway.

274
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:55,461
Take it off now.

275
00:09:55,462 --> 00:09:57,630
(Hold me.)

276
00:09:58,798 --> 00:10:00,198
It's okay.

277
00:10:00,198 --> 00:10:02,098
(Yu Jun bursts into tears.)

278
00:10:02,098 --> 00:10:03,831
That's too bad!

279
00:10:04,264 --> 00:10:05,431
- He didn't pee.
- Got it.

280
00:10:05,431 --> 00:10:06,364
Okay. Let's go.

281
00:10:08,464 --> 00:10:10,731
Wait. What's this song?

282
00:10:11,198 --> 00:10:12,698
He recognized it.

283
00:10:13,898 --> 00:10:16,498
- That's so fascinating.
- Hey, you should carry him inside.

284
00:10:16,498 --> 00:10:19,064
- Turns out our song really was the key.
- Seriously.

285
00:10:19,252 --> 00:10:20,373
Look at that.

286
00:10:20,398 --> 00:10:21,898
(I love this song.)

287
00:10:23,162 --> 00:10:24,296
Let's go, Yu Jun.

288
00:10:24,296 --> 00:10:25,162
This song is insanely good.

289
00:10:25,396 --> 00:10:26,862
Yu Jun, it isn't shopping time.

290
00:10:26,862 --> 00:10:28,462
(Now that I feel better,
let me take a little stroll.)

291
00:10:28,462 --> 00:10:30,862
Parents everywhere, our song really works.

292
00:10:30,862 --> 00:10:32,929
If you play this song,
your baby stops crying.

293
00:10:34,196 --> 00:10:35,829
(Let's head inside
and play in the bubble bath.)

294
00:10:35,829 --> 00:10:37,129
He really stopped crying!

295
00:10:37,129 --> 00:10:38,996
Let's go.

296
00:10:39,796 --> 00:10:40,729
This is nice.

297
00:10:41,362 --> 00:10:42,829
Yu Jun, look at that.

298
00:10:42,829 --> 00:10:45,462
What's this?

299
00:10:46,662 --> 00:10:47,829
Here he comes.

300
00:10:47,829 --> 00:10:49,696
(Your bubble bath is ready, sir.)

301
00:10:49,696 --> 00:10:51,296
- Yu Jun, what's this?
- Yu Jun, let me put you in.

302
00:10:53,496 --> 00:10:55,429
(Crying)

303
00:10:56,562 --> 00:10:58,796
Something got on your butt, Yu Jun.

304
00:11:00,262 --> 00:11:02,529
Yu Jun, your butt can't be on camera.

305
00:11:03,729 --> 00:11:05,729
(His butt is blurred out with bubbles.)

306
00:11:05,729 --> 00:11:06,596
There you go.

307
00:11:07,396 --> 00:11:09,962
(Yu Jun's bubble tail has appeared.)

308
00:11:09,962 --> 00:11:14,329
What's wrong?

309
00:11:14,329 --> 00:11:15,529
Just sit him down in the bath.

310
00:11:15,529 --> 00:11:16,396
Careful over here.

311
00:11:18,029 --> 00:11:18,962
(He enters the bath anyway.)

312
00:11:18,962 --> 00:11:20,762
It's so warm, right?

313
00:11:21,162 --> 00:11:23,662
Let's take a bath.

314
00:11:24,862 --> 00:11:27,129
Let's get you washed up.
Careful, it's slippery.

315
00:11:27,129 --> 00:11:30,762
(Get me out of here right now!)

316
00:11:32,229 --> 00:11:36,362
(Yu Jun doesn't seem
to want to stop crying.)

317
00:11:36,362 --> 00:11:37,262
What should we do now?

318
00:11:40,362 --> 00:11:41,862
YEONJUN likes this so much!

319
00:11:42,621 --> 00:11:44,154
YEONJUN loves taking a bath!

320
00:11:44,762 --> 00:11:46,062
YEONJUN loves baths!

321
00:11:46,062 --> 00:11:47,229
- What's that, Yu Jun?
- Yes!

322
00:11:49,029 --> 00:11:50,129
So interesting!

323
00:11:50,562 --> 00:11:53,396
(The uncles do their very best
to help Yu Jun enjoy bath time.)

324
00:11:53,396 --> 00:11:54,662
I love this so much!

325
00:11:54,662 --> 00:11:56,596
(Yu Jun debates whether to play or not.)

326
00:11:56,596 --> 00:11:57,829
That looks so fun.

327
00:11:59,362 --> 00:12:02,462
(I choose not to.)

328
00:12:03,496 --> 00:12:05,162
Let's just get him cleaned up, then.

329
00:12:07,362 --> 00:12:08,496
(The bubble bath mission fails.)

330
00:12:08,496 --> 00:12:10,096
He really doesn't like this.

331
00:12:11,796 --> 00:12:13,529
We'll try again next time, Yu Jun.

332
00:12:14,962 --> 00:12:15,796
Why is he crying?

333
00:12:16,629 --> 00:12:17,696
You didn't even start yet?

334
00:12:17,696 --> 00:12:19,429
- He really doesn't want it.
- He doesn't?

335
00:12:19,429 --> 00:12:21,262
- He's even shaking his head.
- Really?

336
00:12:22,662 --> 00:12:25,196
(He's crying on the inside too.)

337
00:12:26,396 --> 00:12:30,762
(Yu Jun and BEOMGYU are
both emotionally exhausted.)

338
00:12:31,596 --> 00:12:35,962
(Another failed mission
after the sand play.)

339
00:12:35,962 --> 00:12:38,162
- Yu Jun, look at me.
- It's okay.

340
00:12:38,162 --> 00:12:40,096
Your uncles just wanted you to have fun.

341
00:12:40,529 --> 00:12:42,462
- Once you put him down, I'll wash him.
- That's sad.

342
00:12:42,462 --> 00:12:46,029
(Let's save the bubble bath
for next time.)

343
00:12:46,029 --> 00:12:47,196
Do you want me to read to you?

344
00:12:47,529 --> 00:12:49,829
Yu Jun, I think
BEOMGYU's really good at reading books.

345
00:12:50,229 --> 00:12:51,362
He's feeling better now, isn't he?

346
00:12:51,362 --> 00:12:54,062
"Happy With a Mic!"

347
00:12:55,029 --> 00:12:56,596
Listen to that! Sounds so fun!

348
00:12:56,596 --> 00:13:00,096
"The ants are running
an errand for their mommy."

349
00:13:00,096 --> 00:13:02,596
"As they walk in a line,"

350
00:13:02,596 --> 00:13:04,729
"bumping into one another..."

351
00:13:06,229 --> 00:13:08,229
"Ouch! That hurt!"

352
00:13:08,229 --> 00:13:09,496
"Sorry!"

353
00:13:09,929 --> 00:13:11,096
(He's completely immersed in the story!)

354
00:13:11,096 --> 00:13:12,662
- That sounded so sincere.
- "Where should we go?"

355
00:13:12,662 --> 00:13:13,929
"Should we go over there?"

356
00:13:13,929 --> 00:13:16,296
"We forgot what our errand was
because we bumped into each other."

357
00:13:16,296 --> 00:13:18,196
"That's too bad!"

358
00:13:18,196 --> 00:13:19,862
- "Excuse me."
- Oh, my.

359
00:13:19,862 --> 00:13:23,462
(Is it BEOMGYU, or is the book itself
just that interesting?)

360
00:13:23,462 --> 00:13:24,662
Where should they go, Yu Jun?

361
00:13:24,662 --> 00:13:28,029
"Ducks go quack quack."

362
00:13:28,029 --> 00:13:30,662
"Goats go baa."

363
00:13:30,662 --> 00:13:33,862
- "Goats go baa."
- He's looking at you.

364
00:13:33,862 --> 00:13:36,562
"Pigs go oink."

365
00:13:36,562 --> 00:13:40,662
"Cows go moo."

366
00:13:41,029 --> 00:13:42,296
Are you calm now?

367
00:13:43,262 --> 00:13:44,262
Feeling better?

368
00:13:44,796 --> 00:13:49,096
- Should we try bath time again?
- What made him so upset?

369
00:13:49,096 --> 00:13:50,262
Was it really the bath?

370
00:13:50,262 --> 00:13:52,162
I think he didn't like getting undressed.

371
00:13:52,162 --> 00:13:55,399
He hated the bubbles too.

372
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:56,996
He shook his head the moment
the bubbles touched him.

373
00:13:56,996 --> 00:13:59,062
- Really?
- I liked it, though.

374
00:13:59,762 --> 00:14:01,196
That's too bad. I really wanted
to try that.

375
00:14:01,196 --> 00:14:03,462
You know, playing around...

376
00:14:03,462 --> 00:14:06,029
and putting a bubble hat on him.

377
00:14:06,029 --> 00:14:07,896
Yu Jun definitely knows what he likes.

378
00:14:08,262 --> 00:14:11,362
- He loves his cart.
- He didn't like the sand play either.

379
00:14:12,129 --> 00:14:14,129
How long will it take to make his meal?

380
00:14:14,129 --> 00:14:14,996
Let me handle it.

381
00:14:15,262 --> 00:14:16,429
I'm hungry.

382
00:14:17,229 --> 00:14:18,762
I'll whip something up for everyone.

383
00:14:18,762 --> 00:14:20,062
Then I'll make the ramyeon.

384
00:14:20,496 --> 00:14:21,496
- No.
- No.

385
00:14:23,862 --> 00:14:26,196
- I know how to make ramyeon!
- No.

386
00:14:26,962 --> 00:14:27,929
No.

387
00:14:27,929 --> 00:14:28,962
You look like you'd be a bad cook.

388
00:14:28,962 --> 00:14:31,429
- You'll probably make something weird.
- I can cook! It's just ramyeon!

389
00:14:31,429 --> 00:14:32,862
He really looks like a bad cook.

390
00:14:32,862 --> 00:14:33,862
No.

391
00:14:33,862 --> 00:14:35,029
Isn't HUENINGKAI good at cooking?

392
00:14:35,029 --> 00:14:35,896
HUENINGKAI?

393
00:14:36,362 --> 00:14:39,762
(Where did HUENINGKAI disappear to?)

394
00:14:40,362 --> 00:14:41,229
That's it.

395
00:14:42,662 --> 00:14:44,729
(What did we just witness?)

396
00:14:45,629 --> 00:14:47,062
That's just how you look.

397
00:14:47,062 --> 00:14:47,929
Look over there!

398
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:50,496
Yu Jun, look who's here!

399
00:14:50,896 --> 00:14:52,696
It's me!

400
00:14:53,996 --> 00:14:55,062
Ta-da.

401
00:14:55,062 --> 00:14:57,429
Yu Jun! HUENINGKAI is so cool!

402
00:14:57,429 --> 00:14:59,829
- Yu Jun, touch him.
- HUENINGKAI, you look awesome!

403
00:14:59,829 --> 00:15:00,796
Touch it.

404
00:15:00,796 --> 00:15:01,996
HUENINGKAI!

405
00:15:02,596 --> 00:15:04,496
He's shaking his head.

406
00:15:04,729 --> 00:15:06,429
- Are you scared?
- Look over here.

407
00:15:07,062 --> 00:15:10,562
- That's so legendary.
- So fluffy.

408
00:15:12,496 --> 00:15:13,496
Look at this, Yu Jun.

409
00:15:13,896 --> 00:15:15,062
- You were inside doing this?
- Yes.

410
00:15:15,062 --> 00:15:18,429
I tried making myself
a bubble beard too, but it failed.

411
00:15:18,429 --> 00:15:20,262
He's such a great uncle.

412
00:15:20,929 --> 00:15:22,396
He's going to touch it!

413
00:15:22,396 --> 00:15:23,862
- No, he doesn't want to.
- Are you scared?

414
00:15:24,596 --> 00:15:25,929
But it's so fun.

415
00:15:25,929 --> 00:15:26,996
I love it so much.

416
00:15:27,596 --> 00:15:28,762
(I hate bubbles!)

417
00:15:28,762 --> 00:15:29,796
He's scared.

418
00:15:30,629 --> 00:15:32,296
You don't want to do this fun bubble play?

419
00:15:32,296 --> 00:15:33,529
My expectations were so high, though.

420
00:15:33,529 --> 00:15:35,229
Honestly, the effort alone is admirable.

421
00:15:35,229 --> 00:15:37,729
HUENINGKAI, you're seriously amazing.

422
00:15:37,729 --> 00:15:38,962
I really hoped he'd love it.

423
00:15:39,829 --> 00:15:41,429
I can't believe
he actually put bubbles on his head.

424
00:15:41,429 --> 00:15:42,996
I thought he was sleeping in there.

425
00:15:42,996 --> 00:15:45,296
But then he suddenly appeared
with bubbles all over his head!

426
00:15:46,096 --> 00:15:47,162
He's really something else.

427
00:15:47,529 --> 00:15:49,229
Chef, what's today's main dish?

428
00:15:49,762 --> 00:15:53,829
Today's main dish is vegetable fried rice.

429
00:15:54,629 --> 00:15:56,496
I'm finishing it with egg.

430
00:15:56,896 --> 00:15:59,162
First, I need to make Yu Jun's portion.

431
00:15:59,829 --> 00:16:01,062
His will be completely unseasoned.

432
00:16:01,062 --> 00:16:02,162
No seasoning at all?

433
00:16:02,162 --> 00:16:05,529
Are you using organic rice again?

434
00:16:06,829 --> 00:16:08,596
- Yes.
- Organic rice.

435
00:16:08,596 --> 00:16:09,529
Of course, it's organic.

436
00:16:10,096 --> 00:16:11,062
Yu Jun, want to go outside?

437
00:16:11,062 --> 00:16:12,462
Want to go for a walk?

438
00:16:12,696 --> 00:16:14,796
I've got a jacket here.
HUENINGKAI and I will take him for a walk.

439
00:16:14,796 --> 00:16:16,696
I'm going too.

440
00:16:17,762 --> 00:16:21,929
(SOOBIN, BEOMGYU, and HUENINGKAI are
in charge of the walk.)

441
00:16:22,529 --> 00:16:26,162
(TAEHYUN and YEONJUN are
in charge of cooking.)

442
00:16:27,296 --> 00:16:30,262
His mom said not to season it at all.

443
00:16:30,262 --> 00:16:34,662
(They're making Yu Jun regular food
instead of baby food for the first time.)

444
00:16:34,829 --> 00:16:37,929
(The head chef carefully reads
the note from Yu Jun's mom.)

445
00:16:38,129 --> 00:16:41,062
(The sous-chef chops the ingredients.)

446
00:16:41,562 --> 00:16:45,796
(The blond-haired boys begin cooking
for Yu Jun.)

447
00:16:46,062 --> 00:16:48,329
(Oiling the pan first)

448
00:16:48,629 --> 00:16:50,429
(Adding the chopped vegetables)

449
00:16:50,729 --> 00:16:53,396
(Stir-frying)

450
00:16:53,662 --> 00:16:55,562
"For baby food,
vegetables are cooked until very soft..."

451
00:16:55,562 --> 00:16:56,996
"to be as textureless as possible."

452
00:16:57,896 --> 00:17:01,029
(He carefully follows
the instructions in the note.)

453
00:17:03,596 --> 00:17:04,396
Okay, done.

454
00:17:04,529 --> 00:17:06,996
Yu Jun's meal is ready too.

455
00:17:08,062 --> 00:17:09,462
We should cook him some meat as well.

456
00:17:09,462 --> 00:17:10,696
Today, we're giving him
a fine dining experience.

457
00:17:12,329 --> 00:17:15,229
(A steak is essential for fine dining.)

458
00:17:16,996 --> 00:17:20,929
(It's cooked perfectly,
so that it won't be too chewy.)

459
00:17:22,829 --> 00:17:26,762
(He cuts it into tiny pieces suitable
for a 16-month-old.)

460
00:17:28,862 --> 00:17:31,296
(Plating it carefully on Yu Jun's dish)

461
00:17:34,429 --> 00:17:36,400
The quality of his food is
out of this world.

462
00:17:36,401 --> 00:17:37,396
What do you mean?

463
00:17:38,396 --> 00:17:43,996
(Korean beef steak and organic fried rice
with carrots and onions, unseasoned)

464
00:17:44,962 --> 00:17:47,262
Ours is tastier than yours, Yu Jun.

465
00:17:48,029 --> 00:17:49,762
Because ours actually has seasoning.

466
00:17:49,762 --> 00:17:52,562
(Chef TAEHYUN starts cooking
for the adults too.)

467
00:17:52,829 --> 00:17:53,662
(Adding five times more carrots...)

468
00:17:53,662 --> 00:17:54,729
(and onions)

469
00:17:55,096 --> 00:17:56,762
(He even adds extra protein.)

470
00:17:56,762 --> 00:17:57,596
This one's for adults only.

471
00:17:57,796 --> 00:17:59,829
(Finishing it off
with spicy kimchi for the adults)

472
00:17:59,829 --> 00:18:00,996
That looks incredible.

473
00:18:02,529 --> 00:18:05,262
(Yu Jun returns from his walk.)

474
00:18:05,696 --> 00:18:09,196
(Getting ready to welcome the VIP guest)

475
00:18:09,596 --> 00:18:11,662
(The apron is elegantly draped
over his arm.)

476
00:18:11,662 --> 00:18:12,729
Here you go.

477
00:18:13,662 --> 00:18:15,529
That's it. Let's go inside.

478
00:18:15,529 --> 00:18:17,229
- Hey, baby.
- Let's wash your hands first.

479
00:18:17,229 --> 00:18:18,696
Hi, baby Choi Yu Jun?

480
00:18:18,696 --> 00:18:19,596
Yu Jun!

481
00:18:19,596 --> 00:18:21,896
(This is the famous TAE-gles Restaurant,
holder of three Yu-chelin stars.)

482
00:18:21,896 --> 00:18:22,940
The appetizer has been omitted...

483
00:18:22,941 --> 00:18:25,229
since Yu Jun already had
too many rice crackers earlier.

484
00:18:25,229 --> 00:18:26,562
That sounds amazing!

485
00:18:28,296 --> 00:18:31,362
(Washing hands before dining)

486
00:18:33,262 --> 00:18:35,229
- Nice.
- He's doing it himself.

487
00:18:35,829 --> 00:18:37,762
The other hand too.

488
00:18:37,762 --> 00:18:39,196
He's washing his own hands!

489
00:18:39,196 --> 00:18:40,196
Yes!

490
00:18:40,196 --> 00:18:41,396
We made this just for you, Yu Jun.

491
00:18:42,729 --> 00:18:44,329
This looks amazing.

492
00:18:44,329 --> 00:18:45,529
(Today's main course)

493
00:18:45,529 --> 00:18:46,729
You worked really hard on this meal.

494
00:18:47,362 --> 00:18:49,129
Baby Choi Yu Jun?

495
00:18:49,129 --> 00:18:51,462
If you post your meal on Instagram,

496
00:18:51,462 --> 00:18:53,629
drinks are on the house.

497
00:18:55,429 --> 00:18:56,362
(Got it!)

498
00:18:58,662 --> 00:19:00,496
- Open up.
- Open.

499
00:19:01,362 --> 00:19:02,896
(Yum!)

500
00:19:03,129 --> 00:19:05,296
This is so well made.

501
00:19:05,296 --> 00:19:06,662
- Thank you.
- What was your name again?

502
00:19:06,662 --> 00:19:08,729
- TAEHYUN.
- "What was your name again?"

503
00:19:08,729 --> 00:19:09,629
Let's eat too.

504
00:19:09,629 --> 00:19:10,729
- Before it gets cold.
- Is it good?

505
00:19:10,729 --> 00:19:12,696
- Wait, let me wash my hands first.
- Me too.

506
00:19:12,696 --> 00:19:14,596
(The food critic's expression
suddenly turns mysterious.)

507
00:19:14,596 --> 00:19:17,029
- Baby!
- Is it good, Yu Jun?

508
00:19:17,662 --> 00:19:18,996
(One more bite)

509
00:19:19,429 --> 00:19:20,729
It's delicious, right?

510
00:19:20,729 --> 00:19:22,096
Way better than your old...

511
00:19:22,429 --> 00:19:24,196
(Spitting it out)

512
00:19:24,196 --> 00:19:25,762
- Is it too hot?
- It's hot?

513
00:19:26,796 --> 00:19:27,962
Maybe a little?

514
00:19:27,962 --> 00:19:29,962
It's still warm.

515
00:19:29,962 --> 00:19:32,262
Maybe we need to let it cool completely?

516
00:19:32,862 --> 00:19:33,796
(Worried)

517
00:19:33,796 --> 00:19:34,945
What about this? Open wide.

518
00:19:34,946 --> 00:19:36,729
(He tries feeding him a piece of steak,
but Yu Jun refuses.)

519
00:19:36,996 --> 00:19:39,529
(Another attempt with the fried rice.)

520
00:19:39,896 --> 00:19:41,496
(Spitting it out)

521
00:19:41,496 --> 00:19:42,729
- He keeps spitting it out.
- Is it too hot?

522
00:19:42,729 --> 00:19:43,829
Did he spit out the meat too?

523
00:19:43,829 --> 00:19:44,796
Or is it too cold?

524
00:19:44,796 --> 00:19:48,262
(What's wrong with the food?)

525
00:19:48,262 --> 00:19:50,962
(SOOBIN, the professional feeder,
steps in.)

526
00:19:50,962 --> 00:19:53,529
(He cuts the meat
into even smaller pieces.)

527
00:19:54,062 --> 00:19:54,796
Open up.

528
00:19:55,629 --> 00:19:56,562
He's saying no.

529
00:19:57,162 --> 00:19:58,529
But that's expensive beef!

530
00:19:58,529 --> 00:19:59,662
(He makes his opinion very clear.)

531
00:19:59,662 --> 00:20:02,262
Maybe we should've mixed the meat
into the rice from the start?

532
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:03,173
Open your mouth.

533
00:20:03,841 --> 00:20:05,441
- Do you not like it?
- Good boy.

534
00:20:06,377 --> 00:20:08,144
She told us not to season it.

535
00:20:08,145 --> 00:20:09,312
Yes. It shouldn't be seasoned.

536
00:20:09,313 --> 00:20:10,480
But he's spitting it out.

537
00:20:10,481 --> 00:20:12,415
When I tried it, it was too bland.

538
00:20:12,416 --> 00:20:13,616
Should we give him baby food?

539
00:20:13,651 --> 00:20:14,484
Seriously.

540
00:20:14,718 --> 00:20:16,619
Let me heat up baby food just in case.

541
00:20:17,087 --> 00:20:18,621
(Preparing some backup for a good review)

542
00:20:18,622 --> 00:20:19,488
Why isn't he eating?

543
00:20:20,925 --> 00:20:22,492
TAEHYUN put a lot of thought into it.

544
00:20:22,493 --> 00:20:23,560
- Hey.
- Yu Jun.

545
00:20:23,561 --> 00:20:24,661
- It's okay.
- Yu Jun.

546
00:20:24,662 --> 00:20:25,762
TAEHYUN worked hard.

547
00:20:26,197 --> 00:20:26,863
Open wide.

548
00:20:27,765 --> 00:20:29,360
- He doesn't like it.
- It's okay because you're cute.

549
00:20:30,401 --> 00:20:31,201
That's true.

550
00:20:32,369 --> 00:20:36,672
(The main chef is cooling down
the baby food.)

551
00:20:37,541 --> 00:20:40,710
(Will he eat the baby food?)

552
00:20:40,711 --> 00:20:41,944
Open your mouth.

553
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:44,147
(Munching)

554
00:20:48,552 --> 00:20:50,152
- He's eating the baby food.
- Is it good?

555
00:20:50,153 --> 00:20:51,487
He likes it.

556
00:20:51,856 --> 00:20:54,024
- You like baby food?
- He still likes baby food more.

557
00:20:54,425 --> 00:20:56,192
He's not used to regular food yet.

558
00:20:56,193 --> 00:20:57,127
- It seems like it.
- I think so.

559
00:20:57,128 --> 00:20:59,396
(Yu Jun still likes baby food.)

560
00:20:59,964 --> 00:21:03,633
Okay. Since you don't like the main dish.

561
00:21:03,968 --> 00:21:06,403
(He serves the baby food
Yu Jun is used to.)

562
00:21:06,404 --> 00:21:09,472
- We've prepared a new dish.
- Your usual food.

563
00:21:09,773 --> 00:21:11,507
Hey, half of it is at the bottom.

564
00:21:11,508 --> 00:21:13,175
In fine dining,

565
00:21:13,176 --> 00:21:14,810
there's always a substitute.

566
00:21:14,811 --> 00:21:16,412
That's right.

567
00:21:16,580 --> 00:21:18,147
(Here comes baby food.)

568
00:21:18,148 --> 00:21:19,315
He wants to feed himself.

569
00:21:19,316 --> 00:21:20,983
Okay, then.

570
00:21:20,984 --> 00:21:22,418
- Goodness.
- Oh, my.

571
00:21:22,419 --> 00:21:23,252
(A big bite)

572
00:21:25,055 --> 00:21:26,922
That was the answer!

573
00:21:26,923 --> 00:21:27,757
(Baby food is always right.)

574
00:21:27,893 --> 00:21:29,191
- Is he eating?
- Yes, he's eating.

575
00:21:29,192 --> 00:21:30,059
Okay.

576
00:21:30,060 --> 00:21:31,060
I knew it.

577
00:21:31,562 --> 00:21:33,096
(Digging in)

578
00:21:33,097 --> 00:21:33,930
He's loving it.

579
00:21:34,565 --> 00:21:36,599
Should we still feed him baby food?

580
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:38,034
I'll work on porridge.

581
00:21:38,035 --> 00:21:40,570
(Babies usually struggle
when switching to regular food.)

582
00:21:40,871 --> 00:21:42,104
(Eyes widening)

583
00:21:44,174 --> 00:21:46,375
(While gobbling up his food,
he drops his spoon.)

584
00:21:46,376 --> 00:21:47,810
- He's really enjoying it.
- He really likes it.

585
00:21:50,614 --> 00:21:51,714
I'm glad he's eating.

586
00:21:51,715 --> 00:21:52,782
I know.

587
00:21:54,148 --> 00:21:56,152
- I'm glad we fed him some snacks earlier.
- I know.

588
00:21:56,153 --> 00:21:57,553
(Yu Jun's appetite is back.)

589
00:21:57,788 --> 00:21:59,122
Yu Jun eats well.

590
00:21:59,123 --> 00:22:01,858
(Thanks to that, the uncles can relax
and enjoy their food too.)

591
00:22:01,859 --> 00:22:02,725
YEONJUN.

592
00:22:03,735 --> 00:22:05,462
He's dropping half his food.

593
00:22:05,463 --> 00:22:06,396
You're loving it.

594
00:22:06,397 --> 00:22:07,397
(Enjoy!)

595
00:22:07,398 --> 00:22:08,364
Good boy.

596
00:22:08,766 --> 00:22:10,467
It's like glutinous rice cake.

597
00:22:12,436 --> 00:22:15,071
(Smiling with his eyes)

598
00:22:15,072 --> 00:22:17,240
We should wipe his face after this.

599
00:22:17,375 --> 00:22:18,574
It's not like he didn't eat it at all.

600
00:22:18,575 --> 00:22:20,110
I've never seen him spit out his food.

601
00:22:20,770 --> 00:22:22,145
Are you happy?

602
00:22:22,146 --> 00:22:23,446
(I'm happy too.)

603
00:22:23,647 --> 00:22:24,914
One last bite.

604
00:22:26,016 --> 00:22:28,017
Okay. Done!

605
00:22:28,018 --> 00:22:28,951
(Meal time is finally over.)

606
00:22:28,952 --> 00:22:31,654
- You're done.
- He finished.

607
00:22:32,389 --> 00:22:34,323
Today's dessert is...

608
00:22:34,324 --> 00:22:36,625
refreshing and sweet.

609
00:22:36,894 --> 00:22:38,027
That's so cute.

610
00:22:38,028 --> 00:22:38,895
Bless you.

611
00:22:39,163 --> 00:22:42,130
Since he had a heavy meal,

612
00:22:42,131 --> 00:22:44,734
I prepared something refreshing...

613
00:22:44,955 --> 00:22:46,289
to cleanse his palate.

614
00:22:46,637 --> 00:22:48,037
Look at the marbling.

615
00:22:48,038 --> 00:22:48,972
(Dessert time)

616
00:22:49,239 --> 00:22:50,306
What's that? Strawberry sorbet?

617
00:22:50,307 --> 00:22:51,340
Is that gochujang?

618
00:22:51,508 --> 00:22:52,575
He's trying it right away.

619
00:22:52,576 --> 00:22:54,143
I think he can eat that today.

620
00:22:54,612 --> 00:22:55,912
See? He's eating it.

621
00:22:56,213 --> 00:22:58,614
(Smelling the sorbet first)

622
00:22:58,615 --> 00:22:59,949
Yu Jun is so...

623
00:23:00,250 --> 00:23:02,685
- There you go.
- Fruit stains don't come out easily.

624
00:23:03,153 --> 00:23:05,054
Yu Jun, just eat it up.

625
00:23:05,489 --> 00:23:07,023
There you go.

626
00:23:07,725 --> 00:23:08,558
He's bold.

627
00:23:09,259 --> 00:23:10,826
Yu Jun eats Indian-style.

628
00:23:11,128 --> 00:23:12,997
Never mind.

629
00:23:12,998 --> 00:23:14,163
- He'll be fine.
- He has teeth.

630
00:23:14,164 --> 00:23:15,499
(It tastes better
when eaten with your hands.)

631
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:16,899
Chew your food.

632
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:17,900
How many are there?

633
00:23:17,901 --> 00:23:18,734
I don't think so.

634
00:23:18,735 --> 00:23:20,504
- He's taking big bites.
- Yu Jun, slow down.

635
00:23:20,505 --> 00:23:21,671
Wait.

636
00:23:22,239 --> 00:23:23,172
(Licking his fingers)

637
00:23:23,173 --> 00:23:25,007
I feel like he's just swallowing it.

638
00:23:25,042 --> 00:23:25,942
Let me make them smaller.

639
00:23:25,943 --> 00:23:28,611
- What did he eat?
- Yu Jun, slow down.

640
00:23:28,612 --> 00:23:29,512
It must be sweet.

641
00:23:30,180 --> 00:23:32,014
(He finished the baby food
and the dessert.)

642
00:23:32,015 --> 00:23:32,982
It must be delicious.

643
00:23:33,384 --> 00:23:35,451
- That's good.
- I'm glad.

644
00:23:36,120 --> 00:23:36,953
Try some.

645
00:23:36,954 --> 00:23:39,022
- Okay.
- Isn't it super sweet?

646
00:23:39,023 --> 00:23:40,256
The aftertaste is even sweeter.

647
00:23:41,392 --> 00:23:42,959
It's so good.

648
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:44,861
(Enjoying the dessert like Yu Jun)

649
00:23:45,963 --> 00:23:47,530
(What happened to the strawberries?)

650
00:23:47,531 --> 00:23:48,964
Where did it go?

651
00:23:48,965 --> 00:23:50,633
- Is it good?
- No.

652
00:23:50,634 --> 00:23:52,135
It's the sweetest by far.

653
00:23:52,136 --> 00:23:53,736
Yu Jun, here's a refill.

654
00:23:55,406 --> 00:23:57,500
(Reaching for the refill right away)

655
00:23:57,775 --> 00:23:59,242
(Munching)

656
00:23:59,843 --> 00:24:01,577
This place has great desserts.

657
00:24:02,212 --> 00:24:02,978
Hey, it's good.

658
00:24:02,979 --> 00:24:04,180
(SOOBIN cuts it into smaller pieces.)

659
00:24:04,181 --> 00:24:05,375
- The strawberries?
- Why is it so sweet?

660
00:24:06,383 --> 00:24:07,516
Help yourself.

661
00:24:07,517 --> 00:24:08,784
(Eating more strawberries)

662
00:24:08,785 --> 00:24:09,819
- Isn't it sweet?
- Yes.

663
00:24:10,487 --> 00:24:11,454
It's delicious.

664
00:24:11,455 --> 00:24:13,823
You're just like me when I was little.

665
00:24:13,824 --> 00:24:15,925
(I'm not eating my hand.
I'm eating strawberries.)

666
00:24:15,926 --> 00:24:17,259
You're enjoying your food like a piggy.

667
00:24:17,928 --> 00:24:18,995
Yu Jun, are you a piggy?

668
00:24:18,996 --> 00:24:20,596
(I'll eat it all, down to the last bite.)

669
00:24:20,597 --> 00:24:22,398
- You're done.
- There was a piggy in the book.

670
00:24:22,399 --> 00:24:23,466
Yu Jun, there's nothing left.

671
00:24:23,467 --> 00:24:25,568
(I want the juice!)

672
00:24:27,037 --> 00:24:29,972
This is just juice. Let it go.

673
00:24:31,275 --> 00:24:33,109
(A lingering gaze)

674
00:24:33,110 --> 00:24:34,144
Did you enjoy your food?

675
00:24:36,013 --> 00:24:40,817
(Easing his regret by drinking water)

676
00:24:40,818 --> 00:24:42,385
Yu Jun, in 1, 2, 3.

677
00:24:42,386 --> 00:24:44,454
(Cleanup time after the meal)

678
00:24:44,988 --> 00:24:47,956
(Crumbs fall all over the place.)

679
00:24:47,957 --> 00:24:49,959
Did you enjoy your meal?

680
00:24:49,960 --> 00:24:51,360
Let me wipe it.

681
00:24:51,729 --> 00:24:52,595
Where are the tissues?

682
00:24:52,896 --> 00:24:53,729
Take that with you.

683
00:24:53,730 --> 00:24:55,965
(Yu Jun leaves to take a bath.)

684
00:24:55,966 --> 00:24:57,033
I don't know what to do.

685
00:24:57,034 --> 00:24:59,235
Did you like your food?

686
00:24:59,236 --> 00:25:00,169
(The table is a total mess.)

687
00:25:00,194 --> 00:25:01,761
(I'm counting on you, Uncles.)

688
00:25:03,907 --> 00:25:06,675
(These three are not motivated
to clean up.)

689
00:25:07,277 --> 00:25:08,410
Thanks, Yu Jun.

690
00:25:09,179 --> 00:25:10,479
Do we have a dustpan here?

691
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:13,182
(Yu Jun, the uncles are happy.)

692
00:25:13,183 --> 00:25:16,585
(Probably)

693
00:25:16,787 --> 00:25:20,022
(The cleanup team is enjoying their time.)

694
00:25:20,591 --> 00:25:21,991
Yu Jun, okay.

695
00:25:21,992 --> 00:25:24,394
- You're not taking a bath.
- You won't take a bath.

696
00:25:24,868 --> 00:25:27,436
No. You got the wrong idea.

697
00:25:27,865 --> 00:25:29,065
It's dirty.

698
00:25:29,066 --> 00:25:30,733
- Okay, Yu Jun.
- All right.

699
00:25:30,734 --> 00:25:32,302
Mom!

700
00:25:32,303 --> 00:25:34,537
- "Mom."
- Mom!

701
00:25:34,538 --> 00:25:37,006
(This time we have to give him a bath.)

702
00:25:37,007 --> 00:25:39,042
(Crying)

703
00:25:39,043 --> 00:25:41,611
- We have no choice. We have to do it.
- Yu Jun, we have no choice.

704
00:25:41,612 --> 00:25:42,412
I know.

705
00:25:42,413 --> 00:25:44,414
(Washing Yu Jun, who's covered
in baby food and strawberries)

706
00:25:44,882 --> 00:25:45,715
There you go.

707
00:25:45,716 --> 00:25:46,916
He even peed.

708
00:25:47,718 --> 00:25:48,718
He needs to freshen up anyway.

709
00:25:49,586 --> 00:25:51,887
All right. Good boy, Yu Jun.

710
00:25:52,222 --> 00:25:54,023
Good boy.

711
00:25:54,024 --> 00:25:55,124
(Endless compliments)

712
00:25:55,125 --> 00:25:57,259
There you go.

713
00:25:57,260 --> 00:25:58,060
(Washing him quickly)

714
00:25:58,061 --> 00:26:00,196
(Moving his hands twice as fast)

715
00:26:00,197 --> 00:26:01,931
Can I turn this on?

716
00:26:01,932 --> 00:26:03,245
(They each have
different responsibilities.)

717
00:26:03,246 --> 00:26:04,501
It's hot. Be careful.

718
00:26:04,502 --> 00:26:06,335
(I want to get out.)

719
00:26:06,336 --> 00:26:07,069
Yu Jun, your hand.

720
00:26:08,272 --> 00:26:10,173
(The uncles work together in a crisis.)

721
00:26:10,174 --> 00:26:11,809
I'm sorry.

722
00:26:12,376 --> 00:26:14,243
Uncle is sorry.

723
00:26:14,244 --> 00:26:15,445
(Yu Jun is bathing in tears.)

724
00:26:15,446 --> 00:26:17,547
Yu Jun, look at this.

725
00:26:18,382 --> 00:26:20,984
(Watery eyes)

726
00:26:23,553 --> 00:26:28,057
(Finally, Yu Jun is out of the shower.)

727
00:26:28,492 --> 00:26:32,295
(He has "Stick With You" ready
to make him stop crying.)

728
00:26:33,964 --> 00:26:34,964
Mom!

729
00:26:34,965 --> 00:26:37,466
(It doesn't work.)

730
00:26:37,467 --> 00:26:38,334
Good job.

731
00:26:38,335 --> 00:26:40,970
(Getting him ready for lotion)

732
00:26:41,839 --> 00:26:42,639
Fine.

733
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:43,973
(Zoned out)

734
00:26:43,974 --> 00:26:44,707
Done.

735
00:26:44,708 --> 00:26:48,144
(Where am I? Who am I?)

736
00:26:48,512 --> 00:26:51,114
(Quickly getting the lotion ready)

737
00:26:51,581 --> 00:26:52,481
It's okay.

738
00:26:52,482 --> 00:26:53,916
(Putting on lotion gently)

739
00:26:53,917 --> 00:26:54,750
It's all right.

740
00:26:55,219 --> 00:26:59,189
(Applying lotion thoroughly)

741
00:26:59,523 --> 00:27:01,958
(Relaxed)

742
00:27:01,959 --> 00:27:03,092
Yu Jun, shall we turn around?

743
00:27:03,894 --> 00:27:04,660
Turn around.
(Turning around automatically)

744
00:27:05,562 --> 00:27:06,462
That's right.

745
00:27:06,997 --> 00:27:08,398
- You're good at this.
- Good job.

746
00:27:08,399 --> 00:27:09,165
(Enlightened)

747
00:27:09,166 --> 00:27:12,335
BEOMGYU knows how to take care
of a baby now.

748
00:27:12,336 --> 00:27:15,105
(Thanks to BEOMGYU,
he can put lotion on his back as well.)

749
00:27:15,106 --> 00:27:16,205
In one easy swoop.

750
00:27:17,574 --> 00:27:19,141
- Done!
- Done!

751
00:27:19,142 --> 00:27:20,809
- Yu Jun, you're done.
- Done!

752
00:27:21,078 --> 00:27:21,844
Good work.

753
00:27:21,845 --> 00:27:23,713
(Let's go outside.)

754
00:27:25,082 --> 00:27:28,851
(Finally, there's peace.)

755
00:27:29,019 --> 00:27:31,320
(Finally, they can rest.)

756
00:27:31,321 --> 00:27:37,426
- Something is very wrong
- Something is very wrong

757
00:27:37,527 --> 00:27:41,196
(Exhausted after feeding, bathing,
and dressing Yu Jun)

758
00:27:41,265 --> 00:27:43,733
(There's nothing easy about parenting.)

759
00:27:43,734 --> 00:27:46,269
Are we going to Incheon Airport from here?

760
00:27:46,270 --> 00:27:47,170
- Yes.
- Yes.

761
00:27:47,171 --> 00:27:48,338
(Heading to see off YEONJUN)

762
00:27:48,339 --> 00:27:50,440
Baby Yu Jun, shall we go?

763
00:27:50,441 --> 00:27:51,374
Baby!

764
00:27:51,775 --> 00:27:53,809
Yu Jun, shall we just go abroad together?

765
00:27:56,813 --> 00:27:58,881
(Selfie time with Yu Jun before leaving)

766
00:28:00,684 --> 00:28:04,754
(He takes pictures so he can look at them
when he misses Yu Jun.)

767
00:28:06,523 --> 00:28:08,591
(Touching Yu Jun's soft cheeks)

768
00:28:10,961 --> 00:28:13,396
(Once is not enough!)

769
00:28:13,397 --> 00:28:14,230
Does it hurt?

770
00:28:15,098 --> 00:28:16,398
(I'll get you back!)

771
00:28:16,399 --> 00:28:17,199
What was that?

772
00:28:17,834 --> 00:28:18,700
You bit me.

773
00:28:20,437 --> 00:28:22,972
(Even though you bit me, I can't stop.)

774
00:28:23,407 --> 00:28:25,608
(Yawning)

775
00:28:27,911 --> 00:28:30,212
(Yu Jun is sleepy.)

776
00:28:32,916 --> 00:28:36,619
(His yawns are so cute.)

777
00:28:36,620 --> 00:28:37,820
Are you sleepy?

778
00:28:42,726 --> 00:28:44,627
(YEONJUN, are you sleeping?)

779
00:28:47,064 --> 00:28:48,332
(I'm falling asleep too.)

780
00:28:48,333 --> 00:28:50,033
(No, I'm not going to sleep!)

781
00:28:52,702 --> 00:28:54,269
(Playing with the uncle's hair)

782
00:28:54,270 --> 00:28:56,071
(It poked me.)

783
00:28:57,707 --> 00:28:59,841
(Let me play with it again.)

784
00:29:04,648 --> 00:29:09,252
(Affectionate)

785
00:29:11,588 --> 00:29:12,521
Wink.

786
00:29:16,927 --> 00:29:22,999
(Closing his eyes)

787
00:29:35,078 --> 00:29:39,014
(Now they're arriving at the airport.)

788
00:29:39,649 --> 00:29:40,515
There are so many people.

789
00:29:40,917 --> 00:29:41,850
That's more than I thought.

790
00:29:45,489 --> 00:29:46,389
Do we get out?

791
00:29:49,826 --> 00:29:53,195
(Yu Jun will see YEONJUN off with them.)

792
00:29:53,597 --> 00:29:54,864
Yu Jun, say hello.

793
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:58,100
"Hello."

794
00:29:59,002 --> 00:30:00,269
Yu Jun, say hello to them.

795
00:30:00,270 --> 00:30:02,571
(Hi, Yu Jun.)

796
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:04,273
(A peck)

797
00:30:07,077 --> 00:30:08,210
What's that?

798
00:30:09,079 --> 00:30:11,114
- Wave, Yu Jun.
- Bye.

799
00:30:11,115 --> 00:30:12,681
- I'm going.
- "Bye, Uncle."

800
00:30:13,049 --> 00:30:14,383
(Giving him another peck)

801
00:30:14,584 --> 00:30:16,451
- I'm going.
- Bye.

802
00:30:16,787 --> 00:30:17,553
- Bye.
- Bye.

803
00:30:17,554 --> 00:30:19,122
(Saying goodbye to the members
before leaving Korea)

804
00:30:19,390 --> 00:30:20,256
He's not even crying.

805
00:30:20,257 --> 00:30:22,291
(YEONJUN can't leave easily.)

806
00:30:22,592 --> 00:30:23,559
You're not crying.

807
00:30:23,560 --> 00:30:24,826
(Bye.)

808
00:30:24,827 --> 00:30:25,661
YEONJUN.

809
00:30:25,662 --> 00:30:26,728
Okay.

810
00:30:26,729 --> 00:30:27,996
(He keeps looking back as he's sad.)

811
00:30:28,138 --> 00:30:28,998
The bag.

812
00:30:29,533 --> 00:30:31,000
Let's put the bag in the middle, then.

813
00:30:31,001 --> 00:30:33,218
(I'll earn a lot of money
so I can buy you lots of rice crackers.)
